sentences: Hansjörg Schellenberger is a German oboist and conductor born in 1948.
In the seventies he was soloist of the Cologne Radio Orchestra and from 1980-2001 of the Berlin Philharmonic Orchestra.
Between 1980 and 2001 he has played under conductors such as Karajan, Leinsdorf, Giulini, Muti, Mehta and Abbado.
From 1981 to 1991 he taught at the Berlin Music Academy.
Currently he is principal professor of oboe at the Reina Sofía School of Music in Madrid.
In 1991 Schellenberger founded the Berliner-Hadyn-Konzerte cycle, which he continues to conduct himself.
From the 2021/22 season, Hansjörg Schellenberger will be chief conductor and artistic director of the Berliner Symphoniker.
